names.fullName: The EHEC-host interactome reveals novel targets for the translocated intimin receptor

attributeList.attribute: Each bait was fused to the GAL4-DBD (DNA binding domain of the GAL4 transcription factor) on both its N- and C-terminus. Two different prey screening libraries consisted of a single pool of over 10,000 individual human protein-coding ORFs that were either fused C- or N-terminally to the AD (activation domain) of GAL4. The N- and C-terminally-tagged effector bait constructs were then screened individually against both ORFeome libraries to increase the detection sensitivity as well as against a cDNA prey library (Human Universal). These screens resulted in 1,025 positive yeast colonies from which 328 unique EHEC bait-human prey pairs were identified. 207 pairs with prey sequences that were not located in the protein coding region of genes or interactions including prey proteins known to interact non-selectively with many different bait proteins were removed. In the final dataset, all PPIs that were isolated multiple times, as well as those that were independently reproduced were included.
One additional interaction EspG (ECs4590) with ‘‘Hs.658052’’ (UGID:2727370) was recorded but the identitiy of the human protein could not be traced.
